[1] WHO: only 2 cases during the past week
Date: 6 Aug 2015
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/ebola-update-2-cases-reported-last-week-lowest-weekly-total-in-17-months-89350


The good news coming out of West Africa is that after a year and a half, we are seeing dramatically lower new cases; in fact, last week marked a 3rd consecutive decline in weekly case incidence.

Officials with the World Health Organization (WHO) report only 2 cases during the past week (one each in Sierra Leone and Guinea), making it the lowest weekly total to have been reported since March 2014.

In addition, for the 1st time in 3 weeks, no health worker infections were reported from any of the affected countries... - more]

[Byline: Robert Herriman]

